The paper deals with the existence of Maximum Distance Separable (MDS) codes with specified supports, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also proposes a combinatorial approach to tackle the conjecture, which involves the study of sets and their intersections, making it relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the application of MDS codes in distributed networks, which falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves the study of sparse generator matrices, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with the numerical verification of the conjecture, which involves simulations and experiments, making it relevant to the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
